WEBVTT

00:07.007 --> 00:09.072
<i>♪ I wake up today,
it's a beautiful day ♪</i>

00:09.096 --> 00:11.422
<i>♪ Like the sunshine
somehow removing the pain ♪</i>

00:11.446 --> 00:13.598
<i>♪ I'm vibing away to
the music I play ♪</i>

00:13.622 --> 00:15.817
<i>♪ Reinventing a great jam,
I'm feeling so great ♪</i>

00:15.841 --> 00:18.081
<i>♪ It's a beautiful world
outside my window ♪</i>

00:18.105 --> 00:20.300
<i>♪ I'm in touch with my sense,
just feeling the wind blow ♪</i>

00:20.324 --> 00:22.476
<i>♪ Ease back, lean back,
whenever you feel low ♪</i>

00:22.500 --> 00:25.088
<i>♪ Just remember that the
world's your oyster, you know ♪</i>

00:25.112 --> 00:27.177
<i>♪ Now's the time,
now it's your turn ♪</i>

00:27.201 --> 00:29.396
<i>♪ There's a fire inside,
you're feeling that burn ♪</i>

00:29.420 --> 00:31.790
Father, I know you're very busy,

00:31.814 --> 00:34.227
but may I have a word with you?

00:34.251 --> 00:39.039
Yes, my dear, I always
have time for my daughter.

00:40.344 --> 00:43.782
Whatever you need, just name
it, and it shall be yours.

00:45.393 --> 00:47.980
Even a prince?

00:48.004 --> 00:50.789
Not this again.

00:51.747 --> 00:53.942
With all due respect, father,

00:53.966 --> 00:56.597
I've done as you've
asked all my life.

00:56.621 --> 00:58.860
You know nothing
can take your place,

00:58.884 --> 01:00.949
or the place of our kingdom.

01:00.973 --> 01:05.257
But it's such a big world,
and there are so many things

01:05.282 --> 01:07.173
out there I have yet to learn,

01:07.197 --> 01:10.809
so many places to see
and people to meet.

01:11.723 --> 01:14.224
And dangers to face.

01:14.248 --> 01:17.009
Which you've
prepared me well for.

01:17.033 --> 01:18.315
I

01:18.339 --> 01:21.535
Our kingdom needs its princess.

01:21.559 --> 01:24.364
Our young dragons
look up to you.

01:24.388 --> 01:27.019
They'll look up to me
even more if I venture out,

01:27.043 --> 01:30.501
and find happiness
and success on my own,

01:30.525 --> 01:31.328
that

01:31.352 --> 01:33.286
and

01:33.310 --> 01:35.051
And what, my dear?

01:35.921 --> 01:38.074
And love.

01:38.098 --> 01:41.207
Have I not loved you enough?

01:41.231 --> 01:43.427
Oh, daddy, it isn't that.

01:43.451 --> 01:45.516
It's different.

01:45.540 --> 01:47.474
Different, how?

01:47.498 --> 01:49.935
You're still my
little girl, Cai.

01:51.546 --> 01:54.177
Your Majesty, if I may.

01:54.201 --> 01:55.613
Yes.

01:55.637 --> 02:00.076
Well, sire, what Princess
Cai is trying to say is

02:01.164 --> 02:02.402
well.

02:02.426 --> 02:05.362
Come on, Tinker
Toes, out with it!

02:05.386 --> 02:07.407
It's okay, Tinker.

02:09.520 --> 02:12.238
Your Majesty, Princess Cai will

02:12.262 --> 02:14.240
always be your little girl,

02:14.264 --> 02:16.590
but she isn't a
little girl anymore.

02:16.614 --> 02:18.288
She's all grown up,

02:18.312 --> 02:21.358
and she wants to spread
her wings and fly.

02:24.405 --> 02:27.732
Ah, my sweet, sweet
dragon princess,

02:27.756 --> 02:32.040
you must be aware you
have conflicting desires.

02:32.064 --> 02:35.609
Finding the love of a
prince is best achieved

02:35.633 --> 02:39.657
within the safety and
comfort of your kingdom.

02:39.681 --> 02:43.400
Seeking freedom and
adventure is the best way

02:43.424 --> 02:45.706
to delay meeting that prince,

02:45.730 --> 02:50.494
and to risk losing
everything you have.

02:50.518 --> 02:53.932
But father, how will I
ever know what life is about,

02:53.956 --> 02:55.629
if I never try.

02:55.653 --> 02:59.503
Remaining in the kingdom will
give me everything I need,

02:59.527 --> 03:03.507
whenever I need it, but
how will I gain wisdom

03:03.531 --> 03:05.683
if I never know the unknown.

03:05.707 --> 03:09.252
And if I have to strike out
into the great unknown alone,

03:09.276 --> 03:11.384
so be it!

03:18.067 --> 03:19.523
Good day, Durwin.

03:19.547 --> 03:23.135
I see you're busy doing
nothing, as always.

03:23.159 --> 03:26.660
You again, what do
you want, Blister?

03:26.684 --> 03:28.488
I just want to know
if you've any thought

03:28.512 --> 03:31.883
to my rather generous offer.

03:31.907 --> 03:35.278
You mean you're
offer to work for you?

03:35.302 --> 03:37.367
Yes, that's the one.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.415
I have.

03:42.439 --> 03:43.875
You have, and?

03:45.486 --> 03:49.248
And I think it's about the
funniest thing I've ever heard.

03:49.272 --> 03:50.423
Funny?

03:50.447 --> 03:52.164
Yes, funny.

03:54.146 --> 03:55.863
You have a talent, Blister.

03:55.887 --> 03:58.039
You should think
about performing

03:58.063 --> 04:00.651
for the king's court sometime.

04:00.675 --> 04:03.436
I'm sure you'd make
everyone laugh.

04:05.245 --> 04:06.700
Everyone?

04:06.724 --> 04:08.485
Yes, everyone.

04:08.509 --> 04:14.317
Everyone who heard you would
surely laugh their tails off.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.753
Oh they would, would they?

04:15.777 --> 04:17.755
Now, run along!

04:17.779 --> 04:21.019
Durwin's thinking, in
case you didn't notice.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.587
I didn't, I guess
it's easy to miss.

04:23.611 --> 04:26.590
Well, I'm certainly sorry
to hear that, Durwin.

04:26.614 --> 04:30.071
I was so hoping you'd
come along, willingly.

04:30.095 --> 04:31.595
Oh?

04:31.619 --> 04:33.534
But since you won't,

04:34.839 --> 04:38.341
from the plains of war and
the belly of the beast!

04:38.365 --> 04:39.864
Are you casting a

04:39.888 --> 04:42.673
a spell, Wee Dragon?

04:43.544 --> 04:46.087
Oppose me and starve,

04:46.111 --> 04:49.811
but serve me, you'll feast.

